ews and thought-provoking introspection from seasoned journalists such as Christie Blatchford, Timothy Appleby, Linden MacIntyre, Kim Bolan, and Peter Edwards. A critical account of the challenges involved in crime reporting in ethical, informed, and powerful ways, Covering Canadian Crime poses the questions that reporters, journalism students, and the public at large need to ask and to answer.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aCrime and the pressxCanada. 0aCrime and the presszCanada. 0aCriminalité et pressexCanadaxCanada. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh1 aBerry, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDubinski, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdwards, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFatima, Sabah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFreeman, Barbara M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFullerton, Romayne Smith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarada, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaPointe, Kirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLindgren, April, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacintyre, Linden, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcGuire, Mary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcLean, James S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMuzzatti, Stephen L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Grady, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParnaby, Patrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabular